The paper proposes a novel embedding model for knowledge graphs that uses a relational memory network to model relationship triples. This involves using self-attention mechanisms and neural layers to produce a scalar score for each triple. Given this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The other likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper involves using neural networks and databases to model knowledge graphs.
